<bug>
	<id>32650</id>
	<title>Visual C++ 2008 runtime installed even if already installed</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Is it necessary to install "Microsoft Visual C++ 2008 Redistributable - x86 9.0.30729.17" even if it's already installed?</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">Can it be checked if the library is already present?</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">Always reproducible on Win2000 SP4:</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">- Start LO 3.3.0rc2 installer.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.3">- After decompression you can see that VC++ 2008 get automatically installed.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.4">- The LO setup wizard starts waiting for you to press "Next".</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.5">- Click "Cancel".</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.6">- Restart from step1 or by clicking in the setup.exe inside the setup folder.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.7">- Watch VC++ 2008 reinstalling again.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Cesare.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
